aborne Iron Ore Imp","Type":6,"Title":"China Seaborne Iron Ore Imports","MatchCount":null}],"RelatedArticles":null},{"ArticleId":221250,"Title":"Monthly Offshore Renewables Highlights - February 2026","Content":"","Synopsis":"Challenges in the offshore wind sector have resulted in a meaningful slowdown in project investment, though 2026 has the potential to be more positive, with $48bn projected to be invested globally (+21% y-o-y). Meanwhile in the 'wind' vessel markets, C/SOV and CTV rates have picked up ahead of summer, with C/SOV charter rates averaging ~€50,000/day in Europe, reflecting expectations of another tight market and limited vessel availability across the coming summer.","KeyWords":null,"LastUpdated":"0001-01-01T00:00:00","PublishedOn":"2026-02-18T00:00:00","UseContentForSynopsis":false,"Authors":[{"Name":"Clarksons Research"}],"Url":"https://sin.clarksons.net/News/Article/221250","RoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","DocumentLinkRoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","IsSticky":false,"HasContent":true,"ArticleTemplateId":null,"RequiresTrialistOrSubscriberAccess":true,"IsPublished":0,"ArticleEntityLinks":[{"CategoryId":1450,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Wind","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1041,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Analysis","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1042,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Briefings","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1463,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Sector Outlook","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1451,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"RIN","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1429,"ArticleId":221250,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"SIN","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":10318751,"TimeseriesSortOrder":1,"ArticleId":221250,"Summary":"(WOR, OIN, RIN) Freq: A, Unit: Capacity (GW), Active > Renewables > Wind Farms, Active > Renewables > Wind Farms","Type":6,"Title":"Active > Wind Farms","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":10318762,"TimeseriesSortOrder":2,"ArticleId":221250,"Summary":"(WOR, OIN, RIN) Freq: A, Unit: Capacity (GW), In Development > Renewables > Wind Farms, In Development > Renewables > Wind Farms","Type":6,"Title":"Start-Ups > Wind Farms","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":10336220,"TimeseriesSortOrder":3,"ArticleId":221250,"Summary":"(RIN) Freq: A, Unit: $m","Type":6,"Title":"FID > Offshore Wind Investment (With Forecast)","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":558428,"TimeseriesSortOrder":4,"ArticleId":221250,"Summary":"(RIN) Freq: M, Unit: €/Day","Type":6,"Title":"CSOV, 120 Pax, 3-9 Month Charter, Europe, Mid-Point","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":903792,"TimeseriesSortOrder":5,"ArticleId":221250,"Summary":"(RIN) Freq: M, Unit: €/Day","Type":6,"Title":"WTIV Charter Rates, 4th Generation, Mid-Point","MatchCount":null}],"RelatedArticles":null},{"ArticleId":221164,"Title":"LNG Carrier Market Outlook - February 2026","Content":"","Synopsis":"LNG carrier spot rates appear to have found a floor in recent weeks, albeit at very low levels, but are likely to remain under pressure in the short-term amid robust fleet growth. LNG carrier market fundamentals are likely to remain soft in 2026, with continued firm deliveries likely to cap market upside, although 2027 could see LNG carrier market improvement as export capacity expansion accelerates.","KeyWords":null,"LastUpdated":"0001-01-01T00:00:00","PublishedOn":"2026-02-16T00:00:00","UseContentForSynopsis":false,"Authors":[{"Name":"Clarksons Research"}],"Url":"https://sin.clarksons.net/News/Article/221164","RoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","DocumentLinkRoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","IsSticky":false,"HasContent":true,"ArticleTemplateId":null,"RequiresTrialistOrSubscriberAccess":true,"IsPublished":0,"ArticleEntityLinks":[{"CategoryId":693,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"LNG Carrier","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1041,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Analysis","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1429,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"SIN","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1463,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Sector Outlook","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":30622,"TimeseriesSortOrder":5,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: A, Unit: No","Type":6,"Title":"Total LNG Demolition","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":30623,"TimeseriesSortOrder":6,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: A, Unit: ,000 Cu. M.","Type":6,"Title":"Total LNG Demolition","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":49622,"TimeseriesSortOrder":7,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: A, Unit: No, LNG Contracts","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Contracting","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":49690,"TimeseriesSortOrder":8,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: A, Unit: Cu. M., LNG Contracts","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Contracting","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":98804,"TimeseriesSortOrder":9,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: Million Tonnes","Type":6,"Title":"World Seaborne LNG Trade","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":533536,"TimeseriesSortOrder":1,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: W, Unit: $/day","Type":6,"Title":"LNG 160K CBM Spot Rate","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":534728,"TimeseriesSortOrder":2,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: W, Unit: $/day","Type":6,"Title":"LNG 145K CBM Spot Rate","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":542124,"TimeseriesSortOrder":4,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: % Yr/Yr","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Fleet Growth","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":542222,"TimeseriesSortOrder":3,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, SV) Freq: W, Unit: $/day","Type":6,"Title":"LNG 174K CBM Spot Rate","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":547363,"TimeseriesSortOrder":12,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, WFR) Freq: D, Unit: Cu. M.","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Carrier 60,000+ cbm (steam turbine) - % Active","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":548632,"TimeseriesSortOrder":10,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: % Yr/Yr (tonnes)","Type":6,"Title":"World Seaborne LNG Trade","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":548634,"TimeseriesSortOrder":11,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: % Yr/Yr (tonne-miles)","Type":6,"Title":"World Seaborne LNG Trade","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":549402,"TimeseriesSortOrder":13,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: No","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Liquefaction Project FIDs","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":549403,"TimeseriesSortOrder":14,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: MTPA","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Liquefaction Project FIDs","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":902208,"TimeseriesSortOrder":15,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN) Freq: A, Unit: MTPA","Type":6,"Title":"LNG Liquefaction Project Start-Ups","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":12469471,"TimeseriesSortOrder":16,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, WFR) Freq: A, Unit: No","Type":6,"Title":"LNGBV Contracts","MatchCount":null},{"TsSeriesId":12469475,"TimeseriesSortOrder":17,"ArticleId":221164,"Summary":"(SIN, WFR) Freq: A, Unit: ,000 Cu. M.","Type":6,"Title":"LNGBV Contracts","MatchCount":null}],"RelatedArticles":null},{"ArticleId":221140,"Title":"US Maritime Action Plan: Summary of Proposals - 15th February 2026","Content":"","Synopsis":"On 13th Feb, the US Government published its ‘Maritime Action Plan’, providing more detail on planned policy actions to revitalise the US maritime industry. Potential policies include fees for foreign-built vessels carrying imports into the US, investment in US shipyards and the broader maritime supply chain, maritime workforce training and the creation of a US flagged strategic commercial fleet.","KeyWords":null,"LastUpdated":"0001-01-01T00:00:00","PublishedOn":"2026-02-15T00:00:00","UseContentForSynopsis":false,"Authors":[{"Name":"Clarksons Research"}],"Url":"https://sin.clarksons.net/News/Article/221140","RoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","DocumentLinkRoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","IsSticky":false,"HasContent":true,"ArticleTemplateId":null,"RequiresTrialistOrSubscriberAccess":true,"IsPublished":0,"ArticleEntityLinks":[{"CategoryId":12,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Shipping Related","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1486,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Policy","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1042,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"Briefings","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1412,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"United States","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1429,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"SIN","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":1430,"ArticleId":221140,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"WFR","MatchCount":null},{"CategoryId":833,"ArticleId":221140,"Summary":null,"Type":1,"Title":"World Fleet Monitor","MatchCount":null},{"ArticleDocumentLinkId":null,"ArticleDocumentId":969,"ArticleDocumentGuid":"b7ff5c93-4326-40c9-b6bc-fe8997002bde","Location":"US Maritime Action Plan 15022026.pdf","CreatedDate":null,"DeleteStatus":false,"ArticleId":0,"Summary":null,"Type":8,"Title":"US Maritime Action Plan 15022026.pdf","MatchCount":null}],"RelatedArticles":null},{"ArticleId":221067,"Title":"LNG Trade Ramping Up…","Content":"","Synopsis":"For some time, the LNG carrier sector has been poised for a major period of expansion following record investment in export projects and newbuild vessels in the first half of the 2020s. Although some LNG export projects have faced delays in recent years (impacting LNG carrier markets), it is clear that LNG trade volumes are now starting to ‘ramp up’.","KeyWords":null,"LastUpdated":"0001-01-01T00:00:00","PublishedOn":"2026-02-13T00:00:00","UseContentForSynopsis":false,"Authors":[{"Name":"Oran Creedon"}],"Url":"https://sin.clarksons.net/News/Article/221067","RoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}","DocumentLinkRoleRestrictionsJson":"{\"DefaultRestriction\": \"Show\"}